  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the theft of $25,000, combined with the defendant's cooperation and partial restitution, warrants a sentence that balances accountability with rehabilitation. A period of 6 months is sufficient to address the severity of the crime while allowing the defendant to remain employed to continue paying back the remaining restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
